1
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:33,719
Mom.

2
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,359
We're just changing rooms.

3
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:36,000
There's nothing to be afraid of.

4
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:36,519
Come on, Mom.

5
00:01:36,519 --> 00:01:37,959
Let's put your shoes on. Careful.

6
00:01:38,319 --> 00:01:39,120
Come on, Mom.

7
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:39,719
Have you signed everything?

8
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:46,799
Wait, you...

9
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,200
Why are you crying?

10
00:01:48,799 --> 00:01:50,200
She wants to live so badly.

11
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:52,400
She wants to stay alive.

12
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:54,560
No...

13
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:55,719
You're already tearing up.

14
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,680
Once you're in clinical practice,

15
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:57,640
won't you cry every day?

16
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,280
Don't cry here.

17
00:01:59,159 --> 00:01:59,959
Come with me.

18
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:01,000
Okay. Thank you.

19
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:04,120
Doctor,

20
00:02:04,159 --> 00:02:04,879
I'll come back for the things later.

21
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:05,599
I'll help you.

22
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:06,560
Thank you.

23
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:07,719
Come on.

24
00:02:08,159 --> 00:02:08,560
Xiaojing.

25
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:09,759
I'll see them off.

26
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:11,400
We're not going home.

27
00:02:11,439 --> 00:02:11,800
This way.

28
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:16,719
Come on.

29
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,240
Dr. Ye,

30
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:22,879
you helped save Yu Aizhu.

31
00:02:23,319 --> 00:02:24,639
You must've been praised.

32
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,240
We helped a lot too.

33
00:02:26,639 --> 00:02:27,919
Shouldn't you treat us to dinner?

34
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:35,240
Look at you.

35
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:44,879
Yu Aizhu transferred to Cardiac Surgery.

36
00:02:44,879 --> 00:02:45,479
Did you know?

37
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,120
Yes.

38
00:02:47,639 --> 00:02:48,360
So what exactly

39
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,000
did you tell the family

40
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:49,840
about discharging her?

41
00:02:50,599 --> 00:02:51,560
Hu Weiping said

42
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,159
they didn't want surgery

43
00:02:52,319 --> 00:02:53,000
and chose conservative treatment.

44
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,120
He was very clear.

45
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,560
And because of this,

46
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:56,360
I specifically went

47
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:57,719
to speak with both father and son.

48
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,360
His father said the same.

49
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,800
I don't know why they changed their minds.

50
00:03:02,919 --> 00:03:03,680
I'm sorry, Director.

51
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
I didn't handle it well.

52
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,159
I caused you and Director Lin to fight.

53
00:03:09,319 --> 00:03:10,199
It wasn't your fault.

54
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,360
I'll definitely

55
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,120
be more careful next time.

56
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:13,639
All right.

57
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,439
Tell Dr. Ye

58
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:15,960
to come to my office.

59
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:16,680
Okay.

60
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,759
In your first-stage evaluation,

61
00:03:19,159 --> 00:03:20,360
the doctors

62
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:21,199
spoke highly of you.

63
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,919
They praised your clinical skills,

64
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:23,719
said you're smart

65
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:24,680
and learn quickly.

66
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:27,479
But in the satisfaction survey,

67
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,360
patients and families

68
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,400
gave

69
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:30,240
some negative feedback.

70
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,479
They said you seem cold

71
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:33,800
and speak too bluntly.

72
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,639
That's just my personality.

73
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,280
I don't smile much.

74
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,280
When I don't smile,

75
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,400
people easily think

76
00:03:43,439 --> 00:03:44,319
I'm scowling.

77
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:46,199
Of course,

78
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,439
I'm not saying

79
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,719
you have to smile all the time.

80
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,039
But with patients,

81
00:03:51,719 --> 00:03:52,520
soften your tone

82
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:53,719
and be a little warmer.

83
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,000
That's always better.

84
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:56,159
Okay.

85
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:57,960
I'll work on it.

86
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,080
Lastly,

87
00:04:02,319 --> 00:04:03,120
the nurses

88
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,840
aren't very satisfied with you either.

89
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,039
Your overall score

90
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:07,879
isn't high.

91
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,759
I'm a doctor.

92
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,040
Why do nurses get to grade me?

93
00:04:20,319 --> 00:04:20,920
Dr. Ye,

94
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,439
that attitude is wrong.

95
00:04:25,279 --> 00:04:26,079
Our Heart Center

96
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,199
has always valued

97
00:04:27,199 --> 00:04:27,959
doctor-nurse collaboration.

98
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,120
An experienced nurse

99
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,000
can be as valuable

100
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,040
as a seasoned doctor.

101
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,120
When young doctors

102
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,120
first enter clinical practice,

103
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,399
many practical skills

104
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,600
are learned

105
00:04:36,639 --> 00:04:37,279
from senior nurses.

106
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:38,160
Remember:

107
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,360
you must respect nurses

108
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:42,360
and learn from them.

109
00:04:42,879 --> 00:04:43,360
Understood?

110
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,360
Understood.

111
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,399
I'll go, Director.

112
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,639
You're back.

113
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,279
Perfect. Dinner's ready.

114
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,319
Where's Xiaorui?

115
00:04:59,759 --> 00:05:00,360
In his room.

116
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,279
Xiaorui?

117
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:08,959
Xiaorui?

118
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,000
Xiaorui?

119
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:20,959
Playing games.

120
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,000
I think Xiaorui's been

121
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:23,879
a little unusual lately.

122
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,279
Keep an eye on him.

123
00:05:26,839 --> 00:05:27,680
He seems fine.

124
00:05:27,879 --> 00:05:29,160
Mood swings are normal

125
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:29,680
during puberty.

126
00:05:30,439 --> 00:05:31,120
Are they?

127
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,079
But last family day,

128
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,000
he wouldn't go out.

129
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,319
When you have time, take him out

130
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,160
for a walk.

131
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:38,480
He can't stay shut in all day.

132
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,399
Okay, I know.

133
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,319
I'm leaving.

134
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,600
Eat fewer sweets.

135
00:05:54,399 --> 00:05:56,079
Drink more warm water. It's good for your stomach.

136
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,199
Help me think:

137
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:25,519
where should I take your son?

138
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:35,480
Director Sheng.

139
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:36,199
Ms. Ouyang.

140
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:36,959
I'll be going.

141
00:06:37,519 --> 00:06:37,959
Dr. Tian.

142
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,519
Thank you for your time.

143
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:38,920
Goodbye.

144
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,519
Thank you.

145
00:06:44,639 --> 00:06:45,720
Director Sheng, what do you think?

146
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:46,879
Young but steady.

147
00:06:47,319 --> 00:06:47,959
He's talented.

148
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:48,680
Good.

149
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,360
Leave the rest to me.

150
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,000
Are you that sure

151
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:54,720
I want him?

152
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,000
Director Sheng,

153
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,319
if you want to build a valve program,

154
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,920
you need your own echocardiography specialist.

155
00:06:59,199 --> 00:07:00,839
Tian Xiaohu won

156
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:02,839
the provincial echocardiography

157
00:07:02,879 --> 00:07:03,800
competition three years ago.

158
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,439
He also has deep expertise

159
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,360
in cardiovascular and cerebrovascular disease.

160
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,319
He's exactly what you need.

161
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,120
Talent like his

162
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:10,160
won't stay unnoticed.

163
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,480
His technical skills are solid.

164
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,759
But

165
00:07:14,079 --> 00:07:15,160
he lacks seniority,

166
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,000
and he's somewhat rigid

167
00:07:17,199 --> 00:07:17,959
and not very sociable.

168
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,480
Still, I think

169
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,079
for someone as broad-minded

170
00:07:21,079 --> 00:07:22,000
and good at recognizing talent as you,

171
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,639
those little flaws

172
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,199
aren't a problem at all.

173
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,360
He's just an echo doctor.

174
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,959
This gesture of loyalty

175
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:30,519
isn't weighty enough.

176
00:07:30,879 --> 00:07:31,800
I understand.

177
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:33,240
But rest assured,

178
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,399
once you say the word,

179
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:35,600
whatever you need—

180
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,439
medical devices

181
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:39,040
or professional connections—

182
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,439
if I can get it done,

183
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,600
I will.

184
00:07:41,639 --> 00:07:42,480
Let's secure Tian Xiaohu first.

185
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,120
No problem.

186
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:45,839
Would it be convenient

187
00:07:46,519 --> 00:07:47,199
for you

188
00:07:47,199 --> 00:07:49,000
to take a call from our boss?

189
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:49,800
Hello, Dad.

190
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:53,920
You're moving?

191
00:07:57,439 --> 00:07:58,120
How's it going?

192
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,439
I'm too busy this week.

193
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:02,560
How about this:

194
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,160
I'll come when I have time.

195
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:08,360
Be careful.

196
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,399
Those are porcelain.

197
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,839
Handle them gently.

198
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:15,639
Here, I'll help.

199
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:17,560
Is there gold in this box?

200
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,199
It's so heavy.

201
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,519
They're all books.

202
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,560
We're a scholarly family.

203
00:08:21,839 --> 00:08:22,800
Take a break, ma'am.

204
00:08:22,839 --> 00:08:23,600
We'll be done soon.

205
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:23,920
Okay.

206
00:08:24,319 --> 00:08:25,920
For a scholarly family,

207
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:26,759
and a department head like Director Sheng,

208
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:27,680
can't he hire

209
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,759
professional movers?

210
00:08:29,279 --> 00:08:30,160
He always treats us vendors

211
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,279
like free labor.

212
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:33,240
You don't get it.

213
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,440
It isn't about the money.

214
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,080
He enjoys

215
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,519
making us work for free.

216
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:40,519
Think about it:

217
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,440
so many people compete

218
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,600
for the chance to help Director Sheng.

219
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:45,120
If he lets us work,

220
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,399
it means we're still useful.

221
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:46,919
Right?

222
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,559
Sis, that's a great attitude.

223
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:50,399
Let's go.

224
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,000
Hello, Director Sheng.

225
00:08:53,639 --> 00:08:54,600
We're almost finished.

226
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,559
You need it now?

227
00:08:59,919 --> 00:09:01,519
Okay, I'll bring it right over.

228
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,799
Director Sheng asked us to deliver this.

229
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,039
The supply chain processed it as urgent.

230
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:14,720
Okay, give it to me.

231
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:19,559
That's all.

232
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:19,919
Thank you.

233
00:09:31,519 --> 00:09:32,720
I reviewed Yu Aizhu's records.

234
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,440
She really can't tolerate

235
00:09:34,519 --> 00:09:36,120
a median sternotomy or thoracoscopy.

236
00:09:36,759 --> 00:09:38,159
I'm considering

237
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,080
transfemoral TAVR.

238
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:40,320
You're planning an intervention

239
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,200
in Cardiac Surgery?

240
00:09:41,759 --> 00:09:42,559
A valve intervention

241
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:44,120
would be gentler for her.

242
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,159
Yes,

243
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:45,639
but

244
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,480
her baseline condition

245
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,000
is very poor.

246
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,360
If intervention were feasible,

247
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:50,480
Zhou Xiaofeng would've done it already.

248
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,440
Not necessarily.

249
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,879
It's worth trying.

250
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:53,840
After all,

251
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,080
you transferred her here

252
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:55,759
so she could

253
00:09:55,759 --> 00:09:56,679
get better treatment.

254
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:57,799
In any case,

255
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,679
if you operate, I'm confident.

256
00:09:59,919 --> 00:10:00,480
Director Sheng.

257
00:10:00,639 --> 00:10:01,240
Manager Ouyang.

258
00:10:01,759 --> 00:10:02,399
Let me introduce you.

259
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,720
This is Director Lin Yi.

260
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,240
This is Manager Ouyang from Mai'anpei.

261
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,200
You've met, right?

262
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,519
Director Lin, I've heard so much about you.

263
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,080
Director, I think

264
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,279
the risk is still too high.

265
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:12,799
No rush.

266
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:13,799
Let's think it over.

267
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:15,639
All right.

268
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:16,600
I'll be going.

269
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:20,679
Manager Ouyang,

270
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:21,519
thank you.

271
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:23,080
We suddenly ran short of a device.

272
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,399
Good thing you delivered it in time.

273
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:25,840
It's part of my job.

274
00:10:26,039 --> 00:10:26,600
You're welcome.

275
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,480
Come in.

276
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:30,879
What can I do for you?

277
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,279
Since I was already here,

278
00:10:34,279 --> 00:10:35,559
I thought I'd stop by and say hello.

279
00:10:35,919 --> 00:10:36,679
Coincidentally,

280
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:38,360
I overheard you and Director Lin

281
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:39,799
discussing a patient

282
00:10:40,159 --> 00:10:41,320
with a poor baseline condition

283
00:10:41,639 --> 00:10:42,399
and high-risk transfemoral TAVR.

284
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,039
Have you considered

285
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,600
a transapical approach?

286
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:45,960
Transapical TAVR.

287
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,440
There's a very good product now

288
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,240
with built-in positioning tabs.

289
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,320
It can reduce technical difficulty

290
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:52,039
and improve the success rate.

291
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,159
I've heard of it.

292
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:56,120
You distribute it too?

293
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,559
Yes.

294
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,159
If you think it's suitable,

295
00:10:58,559 --> 00:11:00,159
I can also speak

296
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,159
with Director Lin

297
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:02,399
and explain it thoroughly.

298
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,120
Good.

299
00:11:03,159 --> 00:11:04,000
Give him a proper introduction

300
00:11:04,279 --> 00:11:05,240
to our product.

301
00:11:05,559 --> 00:11:07,120
It's all for the patient's benefit.

302
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,480
Go talk to Director Lin.

303
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:11,639
You barely know him.

304
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,000
True, I don't.

305
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,039
But I know a little

306
00:11:14,399 --> 00:11:15,559
about his situation.

307
00:11:15,799 --> 00:11:16,240
I'll swallow my pride and try.

308
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:26,120
Director Lin.

309
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,480
I'm Ouyang Da from Mai'anpei.

310
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:29,559
We just met at...

311
00:11:29,559 --> 00:11:30,480
I know who you are.

312
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:32,799
Are you free this weekend?

313
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,039
My brother's in a different position now.

314
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,159
He needs to keep clear boundaries.

315
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,759
I'll help you maintain them too.

316
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:39,720
And you...

317
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,159
I'd like to invite you

318
00:11:43,159 --> 00:11:44,080
to an event.

319
00:11:45,559 --> 00:11:46,559
What event?

320
00:11:46,799 --> 00:11:47,759
I have boundaries.

321
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,960
I know you do.

322
00:11:51,399 --> 00:11:51,960
Don't misunderstand.

323
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,279
It has nothing to do with our company.

324
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:55,320
I've actually wanted to ask for a while.

325
00:11:55,399 --> 00:11:56,840
We just hadn't been formally introduced,

326
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,159
so I felt awkward bringing it up.

327
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,120
Take a look.

328
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,440
Higher.

329
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:07,519
Patient Support Home.

330
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:15,600
With all these elderly people and kids,

331
00:12:16,279 --> 00:12:17,159
don't you think I look

332
00:12:17,159 --> 00:12:17,879
out of place here?

333
00:12:18,519 --> 00:12:19,919
Not at all.

334
00:12:19,919 --> 00:12:20,799
It's lively. Look.

335
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,399
People supporting each other.

336
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,519
Looks more like a contest in misery.

337
00:12:25,679 --> 00:12:26,320
Well...

338
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,799
You're already here.

339
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,440
You can't stay home all the time.

340
00:12:29,759 --> 00:12:31,120
Why aren't you going in, Director Lin?

341
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:32,960
This must be Xiaorui.

342
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:33,639
Hello.

343
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:35,519
This is...

344
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,480
How should I introduce you?

345
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:38,960
A volunteer.

346
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,279
She's a volunteer here.

347
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,240
Come in. Don't be shy.

348
00:12:42,279 --> 00:12:43,200
Come on, you're already here.

349
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:43,600
Let's go.

350
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,279
This way, please.

351
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:55,960
I never would've guessed

352
00:12:56,639 --> 00:12:57,519
you volunteered

353
00:12:57,519 --> 00:12:58,240
at a place like this.

354
00:12:58,759 --> 00:12:59,320
Whenever I have time,

355
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,679
I come here to volunteer.

356
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,639
Consider it good karma.

357
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:05,879
This place is pretty nice.

358
00:13:06,399 --> 00:13:07,720
I didn't even know it existed.

359
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:08,960
You're always so busy.

360
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:10,600
It's normal you hadn't noticed.

361
00:13:11,879 --> 00:13:12,399
Mom.

362
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:14,600
What is it?

363
00:13:15,159 --> 00:13:17,000
Can I have some apple puree?

364
00:13:17,279 --> 00:13:18,919
You already had milk today.

365
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,360
If you really want some,

366
00:13:20,399 --> 00:13:21,600
just one small spoonful.

367
00:13:21,799 --> 00:13:22,279
Okay?

368
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,080
Okay.

369
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,759
Let me introduce you.

370
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,279
Call him Uncle Lin,

371
00:13:26,519 --> 00:13:27,080
and him Brother Xiaorui.

372
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:28,200
Hello, Uncle Lin.

373
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:29,440
Hello, Brother Xiaorui.

374
00:13:31,159 --> 00:13:32,080
This is my son, Senlin.

375
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,039
Son,

376
00:13:34,639 --> 00:13:36,480
it's Xiaorui's first time here.

377
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:37,759
He's a little shy.

378
00:13:37,799 --> 00:13:39,519
Help Mom look after him

379
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,799
and make him enjoy this place.

380
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,440
Can you do that?

381
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,200
Good boy. Go on.

382
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:46,639
Big brother,

383
00:13:47,679 --> 00:13:50,000
want to make clay crafts with me?

384
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,159
Little buddy,

385
00:13:52,279 --> 00:13:53,000
I'm not very good at

386
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,360
making clay things.

387
00:13:57,399 --> 00:13:57,879
Okay.

388
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,600
Brother Xiaorui is great

389
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:00,360
at crafts.

390
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,039
Go play for a while.

391
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:01,559
Have some fun.

392
00:14:01,679 --> 00:14:02,840
Look how adorable the kids are.

393
00:14:02,879 --> 00:14:04,000
Please keep an eye on him for me.

394
00:14:04,399 --> 00:14:05,440
Only one spoonful.

395
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,399
Senlin,

396
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:13,279
why is he wearing a wristband too?

397
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,200
Restrictive cardiomyopathy.

398
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:20,000
He already has symptoms

399
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:20,919
of heart failure.

400
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,360
Let's walk over there.

401
00:14:26,559 --> 00:14:28,080
Does he know?

402
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:28,919
Who?

403
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:29,840
Zhou Xiaofeng.

404
00:14:31,759 --> 00:14:32,759
I don't know.

405
00:14:32,919 --> 00:14:34,679
I never deliberately hid it from him,

406
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,080
but I never specifically

407
00:14:36,279 --> 00:14:37,639
told him either.

408
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:38,879
Whether he knows or not,

409
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:39,720
I'm not sure,

410
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,120
and it doesn't matter to me.

411
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:44,159
So Zhou Xiaofeng told you

412
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,080
about our relationship?

413
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:48,960
He did.

414
00:14:49,879 --> 00:14:50,879
Dr. Fang knows too?

415
00:14:51,559 --> 00:14:52,120
I know everything.

416
00:14:52,159 --> 00:14:53,200
Xiaoran knows, of course.

417
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,879
Then he must've told you

418
00:14:56,279 --> 00:14:57,480
to keep your distance from me

419
00:14:57,799 --> 00:14:58,519
and be on guard.

420
00:15:06,919 --> 00:15:07,480
This one is you.

421
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,600
This one is me.

422
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,399
Then...

423
00:15:12,759 --> 00:15:14,080
this one must be you.

424
00:15:15,799 --> 00:15:17,240
This one looks a little ugly.

425
00:15:17,639 --> 00:15:18,519
I think

426
00:15:18,879 --> 00:15:19,960
he looks handsome.

427
00:15:21,919 --> 00:15:23,960
I'm handing out little medals.

428
00:15:24,159 --> 00:15:24,600
Big brother,

429
00:15:24,879 --> 00:15:26,440
how many times were you hospitalized this year?

430
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:33,919
Twice.

431
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:35,679
Then you get

432
00:15:35,879 --> 00:15:37,320
two medals.

433
00:15:40,399 --> 00:15:41,759
My mom says

434
00:15:42,399 --> 00:15:43,759
every time you're discharged,

435
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:44,480
it means you've defeated

436
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:45,879
the disease monster once.

437
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:47,200
Good job.

438
00:15:47,559 --> 00:15:48,159
You're amazing.

439
00:15:50,759 --> 00:15:52,639
I'll give myself medals too.

440
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,159
One.

441
00:15:54,879 --> 00:15:55,759
Two.

442
00:15:56,279 --> 00:15:57,919
Three.

443
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,919
Xiaorui seems down.

444
00:16:26,879 --> 00:16:28,440
His mood has been unstable lately.

445
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,600
He keeps shutting himself in his room.

446
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:31,759
So I thought

447
00:16:31,799 --> 00:16:32,720
I'd bring him here.

448
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:34,679
I think support groups

449
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:35,440
like this

450
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,720
would be good for him.

451
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,279
Whether he talks to peers

452
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,679
or younger children,

453
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:40,799
it would help.

454
00:16:42,519 --> 00:16:43,759
He's getting older

455
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:45,000
and more opinionated.

456
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:46,120
A lot of the time,

457
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:46,759
he doesn't listen to me.

458
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,600
I can try talking him into it.

459
00:16:48,919 --> 00:16:49,879
If he agrees,

460
00:16:49,919 --> 00:16:50,759
you can rest assured.

461
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,080
I'll take good care of him.

462
00:17:02,039 --> 00:17:04,160
Earlier, in Director Sheng's office,

463
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:04,839
I heard you discussing

464
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:06,119
that elderly patient with severe aortic stenosis.

465
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,319
Are you sure

466
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:08,319
transfemoral TAVR isn't possible?

467
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:09,680
Water.

468
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:10,359
Thanks.

469
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:12,440
The risk is very high.

470
00:17:14,799 --> 00:17:15,640
What about transapical

471
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,160
TAVR?

472
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:18,599
A small intercostal incision

473
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:20,079
with a transapical approach.

474
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:20,880
We also have

475
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:21,920
a product with positioning tabs.

476
00:17:26,519 --> 00:17:27,000
The problem now

477
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:27,960
isn't the surgical plan.

478
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,519
It's that the family

479
00:17:31,079 --> 00:17:32,519
isn't very motivated to pursue treatment.

480
00:17:34,599 --> 00:17:36,039
Their thinking is understandable.

481
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:37,839
Rather than risk

482
00:17:38,279 --> 00:17:39,039
surgery,

483
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:41,039
they'd rather choose conservative treatment.

484
00:17:42,359 --> 00:17:44,039
But the patient herself is suffering,

485
00:17:44,079 --> 00:17:44,720
isn't she?

486
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,640
Conservative treatment

487
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,559
can only do so much.

488
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:48,839
Actually, the older

489
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:49,920
a patient is,

490
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,599
the more desperately she may want to live.

491
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,359
That desire

492
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,720
is no weaker than a young person's.

493
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,240
Because the instinct

494
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:57,960
to survive is universal.

495
00:17:58,519 --> 00:17:59,759
Yummy.

496
00:18:00,519 --> 00:18:01,039
Isn't it?

497
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:01,640
Yummy.

498
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,359
It's good.

499
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:02,920
All right.

500
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:03,599
That's enough.

501
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:04,440
No more writing today.

502
00:18:04,799 --> 00:18:05,839
We're done now.

503
00:18:07,839 --> 00:18:08,160
No.

504
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:10,799
You're getting bold.

505
00:18:11,279 --> 00:18:12,200
Okay, careful.

506
00:18:12,839 --> 00:18:13,839
Slowly.

507
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:16,359
Good.

508
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:17,039
Eat more slowly.

509
00:18:17,079 --> 00:18:17,680
Slow down.

510
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,240
People often say

511
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:23,079
even ants cling to life.

512
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,759
Whether elderly or young,

513
00:18:26,519 --> 00:18:27,599
born with a condition

514
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:28,960
or struck by illness later,

515
00:18:30,599 --> 00:18:31,880
no matter how fragile a life is,

516
00:18:32,799 --> 00:18:34,079
it still has the right to continue.

517
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:44,400
Director Lin,

518
00:18:45,079 --> 00:18:46,119
you may think

519
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,559
I brought you here today

520
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:48,440
to exploit people's suffering.

521
00:18:49,039 --> 00:18:49,960
I won't deny it.

522
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:51,680
But please believe me:

523
00:18:52,079 --> 00:18:53,640
first, I wanted to introduce Xiaorui

524
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,039
to this support home.

525
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,039
Second, I wanted you to see

526
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,279
that, like you,

527
00:18:58,599 --> 00:19:00,240
I'm also the family member of a chronically ill patient.

528
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,279
We both understand

529
00:19:02,759 --> 00:19:04,039
how hard that is,

530
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,480
and how badly we want

531
00:19:07,559 --> 00:19:08,839
to fight for even the slightest chance.

532
00:19:23,599 --> 00:19:25,279
Outpatient doctor verbally abuses family,

533
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:26,440
with a terrible attitude

534
00:19:26,519 --> 00:19:27,319
and crude language,

535
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,880
and even tries to hit them.

536
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:32,160
What unforgivable thing did the family do

537
00:19:32,559 --> 00:19:33,799
to make Director Lin this angry?

538
00:19:36,359 --> 00:19:37,200
I remember now.

539
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,279
His heart function is fine.

540
00:19:39,799 --> 00:19:40,319
He can have the tooth extracted.

541
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:41,200
It won't affect his heart.

542
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:41,839
Good.

543
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:42,720
Actually,

544
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:44,839
there's nothing wrong with his teeth.

545
00:19:46,359 --> 00:19:47,440
Then why extract them?

546
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,000
He's old.

547
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,519
It's a custom where we're from.

548
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,839
If an elderly person has teeth that are too good,

549
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:54,160
it brings bad luck to the children.

550
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:55,960
Exactly.

551
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,720
Our elders say that after seventy,

552
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:58,720
if you still have a full set of teeth

553
00:19:58,799 --> 00:19:59,440
and haven't lost a single one,

554
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,119
you drain your children's lifespan

555
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,799
and block your descendants' fortune.

556
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,079
So I brought my dad here

557
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:04,759
to symbolically

558
00:20:04,759 --> 00:20:05,839
have two teeth pulled.

559
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:06,559
Exactly.

560
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,799
You're ridiculous.

561
00:20:08,079 --> 00:20:09,240
The old gentleman is healthy

562
00:20:09,279 --> 00:20:09,920
and has good teeth.

563
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,119
That's a blessing for his children.

564
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,559
How could it hurt your fortune?

565
00:20:12,839 --> 00:20:14,200
Drain your lifespan?

566
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,240
The three of you

567
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,039
should go next door to Psychiatry

568
00:20:16,119 --> 00:20:17,319
and have your brains checked.

569
00:20:17,359 --> 00:20:18,599
Watch how you speak.

570
00:20:18,839 --> 00:20:20,039
My father agreed to it.

571
00:20:20,079 --> 00:20:21,039
What business is it of yours?

572
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:21,880
Today, I need one answer:

573
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:23,160
is my father's heart

574
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:24,559
safe for a tooth extraction

575
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:25,720
or not?

576
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:28,039
A moment ago, yes. Now, no.

577
00:20:28,079 --> 00:20:28,759
That's my answer.

578
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:29,440
What did you say?

579
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,599
I'm the doctor. Listen to me.

580
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:31,680
I'm filing a complaint.

581
00:20:32,079 --> 00:20:33,240
She completely exaggerated.

582
00:20:33,319 --> 00:20:33,880
She made things up.

583
00:20:34,319 --> 00:20:35,400
Who brings a parent in

584
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,720
because their teeth are too healthy?

585
00:20:37,359 --> 00:20:37,920
Complain about me?

586
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:38,839
I should complain about her.

587
00:20:39,039 --> 00:20:40,240
Medical Affairs told me

588
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,519
the family

589
00:20:42,759 --> 00:20:43,799
really was unreasonable.

590
00:20:44,319 --> 00:20:45,240
But you didn't need

591
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,000
to get that worked up.

592
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,240
Look how smoothly Oral Surgery handled it.

593
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:48,000
They didn't want to extract the teeth,

594
00:20:48,839 --> 00:20:49,920
but they didn't refuse outright.

595
00:20:50,279 --> 00:20:51,279
They deflected

596
00:20:51,599 --> 00:20:52,240
and sent the patient to Cardiology.

597
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:53,759
I don't like deflecting.

598
00:20:54,799 --> 00:20:56,000
It's pointless.

599
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:56,759
With that temper,

600
00:20:57,319 --> 00:20:58,359
this has probably spread

601
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,519
all over the hospital by now.

602
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,599
No need to guess.

603
00:21:01,799 --> 00:21:02,440
It already has.

604
00:21:02,599 --> 00:21:03,400
All right.

605
00:21:05,119 --> 00:21:05,599
I'll handle it.

606
00:21:05,839 --> 00:21:06,599
You stay out of it.

607
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:07,160
So...

608
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:09,599
I don't have to write anything?

609
00:21:09,799 --> 00:21:11,000
Nothing at all?

610
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:11,920
No.

611
00:21:12,039 --> 00:21:12,400
By the way,

612
00:21:13,279 --> 00:21:13,680
did Ouyang Da come to see you?

613
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,240
Yes.

614
00:21:15,559 --> 00:21:15,839
At an event.

615
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,119
She said she has

616
00:21:17,319 --> 00:21:18,359
a valve manufacturer

617
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,680
willing to sponsor

618
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:20,839
Yu Aizhu's transapical

619
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:21,920
TAVR procedure.

620
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:22,680
They told me too.

621
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,359
And they contacted

622
00:21:24,559 --> 00:21:25,640
a nursing home

623
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:26,279
willing to take Yu Aizhu.

624
00:21:26,319 --> 00:21:27,359
That's great.

625
00:21:27,839 --> 00:21:28,559
Companies

626
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:29,799
do have certain

627
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:30,880
social resources.

628
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:31,559
If they want to do some good,

629
00:21:31,839 --> 00:21:32,880
we should respect that.

630
00:21:33,079 --> 00:21:33,720
Definitely.

631
00:21:34,079 --> 00:21:34,960
Once the family has fewer worries,

632
00:21:35,519 --> 00:21:36,920
they'll be

633
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,599
more willing to accept surgery.

634
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:39,200
That's certainly good news.

635
00:21:39,279 --> 00:21:39,920
You've performed

636
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,079
transapical TAVR before, right?

637
00:21:41,079 --> 00:21:41,759
I...

638
00:21:43,359 --> 00:21:43,799
did a few cases

639
00:21:44,799 --> 00:21:46,000
at another hospital.

640
00:21:48,519 --> 00:21:50,000
If the family

641
00:21:50,519 --> 00:21:51,640
agrees to the operation...

642
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,039
No.

643
00:21:54,039 --> 00:21:54,960
No, no, no.

644
00:21:55,039 --> 00:21:55,680
The cases I did before

645
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:56,599
were all straightforward.

646
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,559
Aunt Yu's condition is complicated.

647
00:21:58,640 --> 00:21:59,160
Our team

648
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,279
doesn't have enough experience.

649
00:22:01,039 --> 00:22:02,240
What if I pair you

650
00:22:02,519 --> 00:22:03,319
with an expert echocardiographer?

651
00:22:05,359 --> 00:22:06,200
Would that make you

652
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,400
confident enough to do it?

653
00:22:10,279 --> 00:22:12,599
That depends on

654
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:13,960
how good this expert is.

655
00:22:15,839 --> 00:22:16,640
I've checked him out.

656
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,359
He's young,

657
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,160
but highly skilled.

658
00:22:19,359 --> 00:22:20,160
You'll know once you work with him.

659
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,079
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

660
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:25,279
I'll ask the family first.

661
00:22:30,799 --> 00:22:31,599
There's no problem.

662
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:32,680
Here's the situation:

663
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,000
we've confirmed

664
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:35,000
the valve device.

665
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,119
There'll be no charge for it.

666
00:22:38,079 --> 00:22:38,640
Also,

667
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:40,160
most of the procedural costs

668
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,519
can be covered by insurance.

669
00:22:42,119 --> 00:22:43,480
That'll save a lot of money.

670
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,480
Thank you so much.

671
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,359
And this nursing home—

672
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:48,880
we asked around.

673
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,240
It's really excellent.

674
00:22:50,359 --> 00:22:51,839
One of my former colleagues lives there.

675
00:22:53,039 --> 00:22:54,519
We wanted Mom to move in before,

676
00:22:54,839 --> 00:22:56,000
but it's extremely hard to get a spot.

677
00:22:56,119 --> 00:22:57,079
We couldn't even get on the waiting list.

678
00:22:57,079 --> 00:22:57,440
Right.

679
00:22:57,599 --> 00:22:59,079
So she can get in now? That's wonderful.

680
00:22:59,240 --> 00:22:59,680
Yes.

681
00:23:00,079 --> 00:23:00,880
The company

682
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:02,000
has reserved a place for you.

683
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:03,759
All right.

684
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,200
Thank you. Thank you.

685
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,000
Then,

686
00:23:06,359 --> 00:23:06,880
Director Lin,

687
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:08,319
we're entrusting the surgery

688
00:23:08,559 --> 00:23:09,240
to you.

689
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:13,599
Is there anything

690
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,279
from Dr. Liu's explanation

691
00:23:14,359 --> 00:23:15,319
that you want clarified?

692
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:16,319
No.

693
00:23:16,359 --> 00:23:16,759
Nothing.

694
00:23:17,039 --> 00:23:17,599
We've reviewed everything.

695
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:18,400
We're placing her in your hands.

696
00:23:18,519 --> 00:23:19,240
We feel completely reassured.

697
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:20,880
Good.

698
00:23:21,759 --> 00:23:22,960
Then please

699
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,359
sign here.

700
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:24,839
Right here.

701
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:25,720
Write your name here.

702
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:26,079
Okay.

703
00:23:28,839 --> 00:23:29,240
All right.

704
00:23:30,359 --> 00:23:30,759
Good.

705
00:23:31,319 --> 00:23:31,759
Then...

706
00:23:32,279 --> 00:23:33,160
we won't take up more of your time.

707
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:34,920
Thank you.

708
00:23:35,559 --> 00:23:36,079
Thank you.

709
00:23:36,839 --> 00:23:37,279
Director,

710
00:23:40,319 --> 00:23:41,160
I'll be going.

711
00:23:46,119 --> 00:23:47,680
This is Cardiac Surgery's first

712
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:48,680
valve intervention.

713
00:23:49,079 --> 00:23:50,400
Should we invite Director Zhou?

714
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:50,960
It would make things

715
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:52,319
a little safer.

716
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:55,400
Sure.

717
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:56,839
Go ask when he's available.

718
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:57,599
Okay.

719
00:23:58,880 --> 00:23:59,839
You're really going?

720
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,279
You have that little faith in me?

721
00:24:02,119 --> 00:24:03,480
Ask anyone but him.

722
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:06,400
He's the one who wanted her discharged.

723
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:10,519
Understood, Director.

724
00:24:15,559 --> 00:24:16,119
Can you believe

725
00:24:16,119 --> 00:24:17,480
they filed a complaint against Director Lin?

726
00:24:17,839 --> 00:24:18,960
They've got some nerve.

727
00:24:19,359 --> 00:24:20,759
It only takes a few clicks.

728
00:24:21,039 --> 00:24:22,000
Why would they feel embarrassed?

729
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,119
But seriously,

730
00:24:25,119 --> 00:24:26,559
Director Lin was so commanding that day.

731
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:28,079
He shut them down completely.

732
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:29,960
The family even tried to hit him.

733
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,680
Director Lin stood up,

734
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:32,960
and they immediately backed off.

735
00:24:33,599 --> 00:24:34,720
What do we call our Director Lin?

736
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:36,839
Brains and brawn.

737
00:24:37,279 --> 00:24:38,920
He curses people and you still praise him?

738
00:24:39,799 --> 00:24:41,079
Have you forgotten when he yelled at you?

739
00:24:42,279 --> 00:24:43,880
He usually

740
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:44,640
tears into me pretty hard,

741
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,559
but I feel much better now.

742
00:24:47,039 --> 00:24:48,359
At least he never yelled at me that badly.

743
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:49,680
So

744
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:50,960
he wasn't targeting me.

745
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:53,279
He simply looks down on all mortals.

746
00:24:54,079 --> 00:24:55,160
You'd better not copy

747
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:56,039
his outpatient style.

748
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:58,359
You don't have his genius privilege,

749
00:24:58,480 --> 00:24:59,960
or his height and fighting power.

750
00:25:00,079 --> 00:25:01,799
If you imitate him badly, you'll be the one who suffers.

751
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,599
I've still got some fighting power.

752
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,000
Okay, done.

753
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,119
You finished that fast?

754
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,799
A discharge summary isn't a thesis.

755
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:15,839
A few lines will do.

756
00:25:16,079 --> 00:25:17,400
I advise you not to keep it too short.

757
00:25:17,759 --> 00:25:18,640
You'll get scolded again.

758
00:25:21,799 --> 00:25:23,279
Eight pages should be enough, right?

759
00:25:25,119 --> 00:25:25,960
Forget it. Whatever.

760
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:35,359
Let's go scrub in.

761
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:36,519
Another day

762
00:25:36,559 --> 00:25:37,359
fighting to protect the human heart.

763
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:38,240
For our patients' smiles and health,

764
00:25:38,559 --> 00:25:40,079
let's give it everything.

765
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:41,119
Let's go.

766
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:41,839
Director.

767
00:25:50,119 --> 00:25:50,519
Can I help with anything?

768
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:51,920
Yes.

769
00:25:52,519 --> 00:25:52,880
Stay away from the operating table.

770
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,839
Lin Yi,

771
00:25:57,359 --> 00:25:57,920
this is Tian Xiaohu,

772
00:25:58,119 --> 00:25:58,880
the echocardiographer

773
00:25:59,599 --> 00:26:00,160
Director Sheng introduced.

774
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,319
Thank you for joining us.

775
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,079
Safety check.

776
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:06,359
Patient Yu Aizhu, age sixty-nine,

777
00:26:06,759 --> 00:26:08,359
medical record number 2062798.

778
00:26:08,559 --> 00:26:10,519
Severe aortic stenosis.

779
00:26:10,759 --> 00:26:12,160
Procedure:

780
00:26:12,319 --> 00:26:12,599
transapical TAVR.

781
00:26:12,599 --> 00:26:13,400
A 25-millimeter valve is ready.

782
00:26:13,599 --> 00:26:14,559
Cardiopulmonary bypass on standby.

783
00:26:14,759 --> 00:26:15,759
Maintain adequate anesthesia to prevent agitation.

784
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:17,000
The patient has diabetes,

785
00:26:17,119 --> 00:26:18,359
so closely manage volume status

786
00:26:18,519 --> 00:26:20,160
and blood pressure intraoperatively.

787
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:20,920
No problem.

788
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,000
Let's begin.

789
00:26:28,759 --> 00:26:29,160
Puncture.

790
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:31,599
Director!

791
00:26:32,119 --> 00:26:32,559
Director!

792
00:27:02,839 --> 00:27:03,279
I'm fine, Dad.

793
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:32,960
The guidewire slipped into the left atrium.

794
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:44,799
Director Lin,

795
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,680
angle the sheath

796
00:27:46,759 --> 00:27:47,680
toward the right shoulder.

797
00:27:47,839 --> 00:27:49,279
That will direct the guidewire

798
00:27:49,359 --> 00:27:50,039
into the left ventricular outflow tract.

799
00:28:13,279 --> 00:28:13,759
Dad.

800
00:28:14,279 --> 00:28:14,680
Come sit down.

801
00:28:15,599 --> 00:28:16,119
You've been standing too long.

802
00:28:16,279 --> 00:28:17,039
Sit down.

803
00:28:22,359 --> 00:28:23,480
Is Guo Xu's family here?

804
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,160
Yes, we're here.

805
00:28:24,519 --> 00:28:25,200
Son, hurry.

806
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:27,240
We need your signature.

807
00:28:40,599 --> 00:28:40,960
In position.

808
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:41,960
Rapid pacing at 180.

809
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,000
Pacing at 180.

810
00:28:46,359 --> 00:28:46,799
Successful.

811
00:28:47,319 --> 00:28:47,720
Balloon valvuloplasty.

812
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:54,640
Withdraw. Stop pacing.

813
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:57,519
Stop pacing.

814
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,160
The left coronary artery isn't opacifying.

815
00:29:05,759 --> 00:29:07,119
The coronary ostium is obstructed.

816
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:08,960
Her coronary ostium

817
00:29:09,039 --> 00:29:10,440
is lower than we estimated preoperatively.

818
00:29:10,799 --> 00:29:11,920
Should we call Cardiology

819
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,000
for coronary protection?

820
00:29:13,759 --> 00:29:14,240
No.

821
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,920
This transapical system

822
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:16,799
has a built-in design.

823
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,200
The patient's native leaflet

824
00:29:18,359 --> 00:29:19,519
and coronary ostium

825
00:29:19,559 --> 00:29:20,480
are protected by positioning tabs.

826
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,400
Director Lin, don't worry.

827
00:29:21,559 --> 00:29:22,279
I'll assist you.

828
00:29:26,359 --> 00:29:27,960
Aortic regurgitation has significantly worsened.

829
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:29,400
Left ventricular contraction is weak.

830
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,519
Her blood pressure is dropping too.

831
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:33,880
It's caused by the regurgitation.

832
00:29:34,599 --> 00:29:35,720
We need to implant the valve quickly.

833
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:36,319
Tianming,

834
00:29:36,599 --> 00:29:37,519
use medication to support her blood pressure.

835
00:29:37,599 --> 00:29:37,960
Okay.

836
00:29:58,480 --> 00:29:59,000
Loosen the purse-string.

837
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,359
Delivery system.

838
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,599
Rotate slightly

839
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:16,359
clockwise.

840
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:22,880
The positioning tabs have entered

841
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,039
the base of the aortic sinuses.

842
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:25,799
Prepare to deploy the valve.

843
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:32,000
The valve is too deep.

844
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,799
Use a little less force

845
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,079
on the hand pulling the delivery system.

846
00:30:35,319 --> 00:30:35,720
Liu Dong.

847
00:30:42,319 --> 00:30:43,000
The depth is good.

848
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,400
The valve is well seated.

849
00:30:56,599 --> 00:30:57,440
No paravalvular leak.

850
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,440
Trace central regurgitation.

851
00:30:59,759 --> 00:31:00,839
Transvalvular gradient: ten.

852
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:03,880
Blood pressure is good.

853
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:20,960
Congratulations, Director Sheng.

854
00:31:21,559 --> 00:31:22,240
And thank you.

855
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:23,119
It's my job.

856
00:31:24,279 --> 00:31:24,960
The purse-string is yours.

857
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:25,720
Okay, Director.

858
00:31:29,599 --> 00:31:30,279
Congratulations.

859
00:31:30,759 --> 00:31:31,519
Little Turtle

860
00:31:32,279 --> 00:31:33,160
won again.

861
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:52,680
Yu Aizhu's surgery was successful.

862
00:33:12,119 --> 00:33:12,559
Ouyang.

863
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:14,079
Boss.

864
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:15,400
It's so late.

865
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:16,240
Why are you still here?

866
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,599
I just finished covering the case

867
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,279
and came back to work overtime.

868
00:33:19,359 --> 00:33:20,680
How did the surgery go?

869
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:23,319
Seeing is believing.

870
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:26,160
Lin Yi truly deserves

871
00:33:26,559 --> 00:33:27,559
his reputation as a genius.

872
00:33:28,319 --> 00:33:29,079
He said himself

873
00:33:29,359 --> 00:33:30,279
he hasn't done many interventions,

874
00:33:30,359 --> 00:33:31,839
especially via the transapical approach.

875
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:34,200
I could tell

876
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,559
his movements were a little unfamiliar.

877
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,039
But he reacted extremely quickly,

878
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,880
and stayed calm and composed.

879
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:40,119
With only a little guidance,

880
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,000
he executed every step perfectly.

881
00:33:41,359 --> 00:33:42,599
By the end of this one procedure,

882
00:33:42,799 --> 00:33:44,240
I think he'd already mastered it.

883
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:45,920
That learning ability

884
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:46,759
is honestly

885
00:33:47,599 --> 00:33:48,200
astonishing.

886
00:33:52,119 --> 00:33:53,400
I was wondering

887
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:57,279
why Sheng Nian would take

888
00:33:57,319 --> 00:33:58,759
an elderly, critically ill patient

889
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,720
with multiple comorbidities.

890
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:02,319
That's the definition of a hot potato.

891
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:04,640
I thought he'd suddenly grown a conscience.

892
00:34:05,359 --> 00:34:06,240
Turns out

893
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,880
he has an advanced weapon like Lin Yi

894
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,079
in his hands.

895
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:10,519
That's why he felt confident.

896
00:34:10,559 --> 00:34:12,239
Not an advanced weapon.

897
00:34:12,599 --> 00:34:13,519
A nuclear weapon.

898
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:14,679
Anyway,

899
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:16,119
Dongli Cardiac Surgery

900
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:17,119
was able to launch

901
00:34:17,119 --> 00:34:18,199
transapical TAVR

902
00:34:18,239 --> 00:34:19,519
because of your contribution.

903
00:34:20,639 --> 00:34:22,079
Hard work pays off.

904
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,559
I saw how determined Sheng Nian was

905
00:34:23,559 --> 00:34:24,480
to build

906
00:34:24,559 --> 00:34:26,199
a valve program.

907
00:34:26,599 --> 00:34:27,159
And conveniently,

908
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:28,519
they had Yu Aizhu,

909
00:34:28,639 --> 00:34:29,480
who happened

910
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,480
to meet the indications

911
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:31,760
and need our product.

912
00:34:32,119 --> 00:34:33,440
So I went with the flow.

913
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:36,360
Earlier,

914
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,719
while I was having dinner with a client,

915
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:40,000
Sheng Nian called me.

916
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:42,760
If Director Sheng is willing

917
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,039
to speak up for you,

918
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:45,800
you must have impressed him.

919
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:47,840
Don't forget to thank him.

920
00:34:48,599 --> 00:34:49,000
Okay.

921
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,280
No matter what,

922
00:34:50,559 --> 00:34:51,679
you've secured

923
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,199
Dongli Cardiac Surgery.

924
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,320
From now on, whether transapical

925
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,199
or transfemoral TAVR,

926
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,239
Cardiac Surgery can

927
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:58,599
perform it on a larger scale.

928
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:00,159
The valves benefit patients,

929
00:35:01,039 --> 00:35:02,679
and we expand our business.

930
00:35:02,719 --> 00:35:03,079
Exactly.

931
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:04,000
You're right, Boss.

932
00:35:04,239 --> 00:35:04,800
Whatever you say.

933
00:35:06,519 --> 00:35:06,880
Also,

934
00:35:07,599 --> 00:35:09,320
since things are going so well

935
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,679
in Cardiac Surgery,

936
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:11,960
you can confidently

937
00:35:12,039 --> 00:35:12,760
leave Cardiology

938
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:13,760
to Qi Qiang and the others.

939
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,800
Don't, Boss.

940
00:35:16,599 --> 00:35:17,400
There are still a few days

941
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:18,559
left in the handover period.

942
00:35:18,599 --> 00:35:19,360
Give me a little more time.

943
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:22,719
You have to keep your word.

944
00:35:23,119 --> 00:35:23,480
Fine.

945
00:35:23,960 --> 00:35:24,519
I'm leaving.

946
00:35:24,719 --> 00:35:25,559
Don't stay too late.

947
00:35:26,199 --> 00:35:26,519
Okay.

948
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:28,159
See you tomorrow, Boss.

949
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:28,639
Bye.

950
00:35:58,480 --> 00:35:59,039
How is she?

951
00:35:59,719 --> 00:36:00,719
The surgery went well,

952
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:02,719
but she became delirious after midnight.

953
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:04,320
Her persecutory delusions worsened acutely.

954
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:05,800
She kept saying someone wanted to harm her.

955
00:36:06,519 --> 00:36:07,559
Her orientation is poor too.

956
00:36:07,679 --> 00:36:09,119
She can't tell day from night.

957
00:36:09,719 --> 00:36:11,039
We used protective restraints

958
00:36:11,039 --> 00:36:12,639
and sedation, and she's stable now.

959
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:14,599
Don't worry. I'll watch her closely.

960
00:36:17,239 --> 00:36:17,840
I'm leaving.

961
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:20,360
That TAVR

962
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:20,880
was well done.

963
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:48,679
Early this morning,

964
00:36:48,719 --> 00:36:49,559
I went to the general ICU

965
00:36:49,679 --> 00:36:50,360
and saw that Yu Aizhu

966
00:36:50,440 --> 00:36:51,320
had been successfully extubated.

967
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:53,239
She was extubated last night.

968
00:36:53,559 --> 00:36:54,440
Her recovery is going smoothly.

969
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:55,320
So?

970
00:36:55,559 --> 00:36:56,480
Dr. Tian is good, right?

971
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:58,320
More than good.

972
00:36:58,360 --> 00:36:59,039
He's exceptional.

973
00:36:59,079 --> 00:37:00,239
He was extremely steady in the OR.

974
00:37:01,039 --> 00:37:02,400
A mature echocardiographer

975
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,000
is crucial

976
00:37:03,039 --> 00:37:03,719
to a TAVR procedure.

977
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:04,400
I'm thinking

978
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:05,440
we should transfer Dr. Tian

979
00:37:05,559 --> 00:37:06,519
to our department.

980
00:37:06,519 --> 00:37:07,480
Then he can work

981
00:37:08,039 --> 00:37:09,400
exclusively with you

982
00:37:09,559 --> 00:37:10,320
on the same team.

983
00:37:11,079 --> 00:37:11,639
That would be great.

984
00:37:13,079 --> 00:37:14,199
What about Ouyang Da?

985
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:14,920
How was she?

986
00:37:16,119 --> 00:37:16,760
She...

987
00:37:18,679 --> 00:37:19,519
was professionally competent.

988
00:37:19,639 --> 00:37:20,920
She just talked a little too much in the OR.

989
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:22,960
But it was the first time I realized

990
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:24,400
how important

991
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:25,639
a product specialist can be

992
00:37:26,079 --> 00:37:26,800
to a procedure.

993
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:27,960
She's more technically skilled

994
00:37:28,159 --> 00:37:29,119
than an average sales rep.

995
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:30,440
She also earned extra certification,

996
00:37:30,480 --> 00:37:31,679
so she doubles

997
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:33,119
as technical support.

998
00:37:33,559 --> 00:37:35,159
If the primary surgeon is a race-car driver,

999
00:37:35,559 --> 00:37:36,599
the product specialist

1000
00:37:36,679 --> 00:37:37,480
is the navigator.

1001
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,119
A good navigator

1002
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,159
can make the driver even better.

1003
00:37:43,559 --> 00:37:44,639
A truly good navigator

1004
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:45,400
should also know

1005
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:46,360
when to speak

1006
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,360
and when to stay quiet.

1007
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:49,960
After watching the surgery,

1008
00:37:50,079 --> 00:37:51,039
I had an idea.

1009
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,239
You should lead

1010
00:37:52,519 --> 00:37:53,840
the creation of a one-stop

1011
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,559
valvular disease program.

1012
00:37:56,039 --> 00:37:56,840
In other words,

1013
00:37:57,159 --> 00:37:58,800
whether a patient needs open-heart surgery

1014
00:37:58,960 --> 00:38:00,199
or a minimally invasive intervention,

1015
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:01,119
we can

1016
00:38:01,239 --> 00:38:02,159
choose the most appropriate approach

1017
00:38:02,199 --> 00:38:03,239
based on the condition

1018
00:38:03,840 --> 00:38:04,639
and handle everything in one place.

1019
00:38:05,519 --> 00:38:06,159
Me?

1020
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:07,719
I don't think I can do that.

1021
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,519
You won't be doing it alone.

1022
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:10,760
There'll be Tian Xiaohu,

1023
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:11,519
Ouyang Da,

1024
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:12,480
and if necessary,

1025
00:38:12,639 --> 00:38:13,360
outside experts too.

1026
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:14,000
Yes.

1027
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:15,280
I'm not worried about those things.

1028
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:18,159
But Aunt Yu's case

1029
00:38:18,719 --> 00:38:20,039
was a special circumstance.

1030
00:38:20,719 --> 00:38:22,320
That special circumstance

1031
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:22,920
is exactly what made me realize

1032
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,440
that for an excellent

1033
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:25,360
cardiac surgeon,

1034
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,400
no technical challenge

1035
00:38:27,719 --> 00:38:29,039
is impossible if he's willing to learn.

1036
00:38:29,679 --> 00:38:31,119
Besides, you passed your assessment

1037
00:38:31,239 --> 00:38:32,000
and have the certification.

1038
00:38:36,519 --> 00:38:36,920
Director,

1039
00:38:38,519 --> 00:38:39,440
at our hospital,

1040
00:38:39,719 --> 00:38:40,760
minimally invasive interventions

1041
00:38:41,079 --> 00:38:42,840
have always been handled by Cardiology.

1042
00:38:43,559 --> 00:38:44,519
I'm afraid if we make too much noise...

1043
00:38:44,559 --> 00:38:45,960
No rule has ever said

1044
00:38:46,199 --> 00:38:48,000
only Cardiology can perform interventions.

1045
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:50,119
Medicine is becoming more surgical,

1046
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:51,159
and surgery more minimally invasive.

1047
00:38:51,199 --> 00:38:52,079
That's the broader trend.

1048
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:53,480
My goal is clear:

1049
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,159
to lead our department

1050
00:38:55,239 --> 00:38:56,320
ahead of that trend.

1051
00:38:57,719 --> 00:38:59,239
You and I must work toward it together.

1052
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:05,119
There's no rush.

1053
00:39:05,679 --> 00:39:06,679
Let's both think it over.

1054
00:39:19,039 --> 00:39:21,159
Is Bed 7

1055
00:39:21,199 --> 00:39:22,119
the transapical TAVR patient?

1056
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:22,840
Yes.

1057
00:39:24,239 --> 00:39:25,039
Is she recovering poorly?

1058
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:26,880
No.

1059
00:39:27,440 --> 00:39:28,679
The procedure went smoothly.

1060
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:29,840
She was extubated that same night.

1061
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:31,320
But she's elderly,

1062
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,440
had a minor stroke before,

1063
00:39:32,519 --> 00:39:33,519
and has Alzheimer's disease.

1064
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:34,639
So we wanted

1065
00:39:34,639 --> 00:39:35,199
to keep her in the general ICU

1066
00:39:35,239 --> 00:39:36,440
a little longer for observation.

1067
00:39:36,639 --> 00:39:38,000
She was much better this morning.

1068
00:39:38,119 --> 00:39:38,639
There should be no

1069
00:39:38,679 --> 00:39:39,679
further neurological damage.

1070
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:42,079
I've reviewed

1071
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:42,840
all the imaging

1072
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:43,559
from this procedure.

1073
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:45,719
I think Lin Yi

1074
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,079
did a beautiful job.

1075
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,719
Given the difficulty,

1076
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,360
successfully completing

1077
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:53,079
a transapical

1078
00:39:53,079 --> 00:39:53,840
TAVR

1079
00:39:54,079 --> 00:39:55,239
was truly remarkable.

1080
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:56,920
If I remember correctly,

1081
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,960
this was the first time

1082
00:39:59,159 --> 00:40:00,960
Dongli Cardiac Surgery

1083
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:01,599
independently performed a valve intervention, right?

1084
00:40:02,039 --> 00:40:02,440
Yes.

1085
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:05,039
You set a good precedent.

1086
00:40:11,599 --> 00:40:12,920
It wasn't my work alone.

1087
00:40:13,519 --> 00:40:14,480
Your leadership made it possible, President Wang.

1088
00:40:14,599 --> 00:40:15,840
Actions matter more than words.

1089
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:19,679
Summarize this case carefully

1090
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:20,679
and send all relevant materials

1091
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,760
to Publicity.

1092
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:24,679
Have them promote it properly.

1093
00:40:25,159 --> 00:40:25,599
Understood.

1094
00:40:25,639 --> 00:40:27,079
I'll arrange it after the meeting.

1095
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:28,199
Good.

1096
00:40:29,079 --> 00:40:29,800
Continue the handover.

1097
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:43,280
Director Zhou.

1098
00:40:44,559 --> 00:40:45,079
Director Sheng.

1099
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:53,360
Director Zhou.

1100
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:54,559
Sorry.

1101
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,119
I haven't had time

1102
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:57,360
to speak with you.

1103
00:40:58,519 --> 00:41:00,039
Yu Aizhu transferred

1104
00:41:00,079 --> 00:41:00,880
from Cardiology.

1105
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:02,639
We were so busy with surgery

1106
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,880
that we didn't get a chance

1107
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:04,519
to notify you.

1108
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,039
That was an oversight on our part.

1109
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:06,840
It's fine.

1110
00:41:07,519 --> 00:41:08,280
Lin Yi told me

1111
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:08,840
right away.

1112
00:41:09,159 --> 00:41:09,639
Good.

1113
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:11,400
I heard

1114
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:12,840
you and Lin Yi had some friction

1115
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:13,760
over Yu Aizhu.

1116
00:41:14,159 --> 00:41:15,199
I hope it doesn't

1117
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,559
affect your relationship.

1118
00:41:17,559 --> 00:41:18,199
It won't.

1119
00:41:18,639 --> 00:41:19,559
You're overthinking it, Director Sheng.

1120
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:22,760
Anything else?

1121
00:41:25,119 --> 00:41:25,719
Director Zhou,

1122
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:27,360
you once said

1123
00:41:27,719 --> 00:41:28,880
that once you set your mind on something,

1124
00:41:29,039 --> 00:41:30,000
you'd see it through.

1125
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:32,880
I'm the same.

1126
00:41:47,079 --> 00:41:47,679
Who was the echocardiographer

1127
00:41:47,679 --> 00:41:48,280
for Yu Aizhu's TAVR?

1128
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:49,679
Tian Xiaohu from Sixth Hospital.

1129
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:52,800
The round-faced one?

1130
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:55,039
I've met him

1131
00:41:55,239 --> 00:41:56,199
at conferences before.

1132
00:41:56,199 --> 00:41:56,840
He didn't stand out much,

1133
00:41:57,119 --> 00:41:58,519
but his skills are excellent.

1134
00:41:58,800 --> 00:41:59,800
Who brought him in?

1135
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:01,519
Ouyang Da.

1136
00:42:03,199 --> 00:42:03,880
She introduced him

1137
00:42:05,079 --> 00:42:05,719
to Director Sheng,

1138
00:42:05,719 --> 00:42:06,679
and Director Sheng personally arranged

1139
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,800
his temporary transfer.

1140
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:10,400
Director,

1141
00:42:11,519 --> 00:42:12,400
I heard

1142
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:14,519
Director Sheng wants to recruit him to Dongli.

1143
00:42:14,719 --> 00:42:15,800
And Cardiac Surgery

1144
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,280
has applied for another echo room.

1145
00:42:21,079 --> 00:42:22,599
This whole series of moves

1146
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:23,639
clearly shows

1147
00:42:23,639 --> 00:42:25,199
he plans to expand into valve procedures.

1148
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:26,199
If this continues,

1149
00:42:26,679 --> 00:42:27,400
what will be left

1150
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:28,199
for Cardiology?

1151
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:32,079
Some overlap

1152
00:42:32,079 --> 00:42:33,119
between departments

1153
00:42:33,239 --> 00:42:34,000
is inevitable.

1154
00:42:34,679 --> 00:42:35,679
Whether we like it or not,

1155
00:42:35,760 --> 00:42:36,639
we can't eliminate it.

1156
00:42:37,320 --> 00:42:38,639
Besides, interventions have a high threshold.

1157
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:40,000
Not everyone can do them well.

1158
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:41,400
In all of Cardiac Surgery, only Lin Yi

1159
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:42,199
has that level of skill.

1160
00:42:42,599 --> 00:42:43,920
But Yu Aizhu

1161
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:44,639
was originally

1162
00:42:44,639 --> 00:42:45,559
our Cardiology patient.

1163
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:46,719
Cardiac Surgery took her

1164
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:47,119
and performed TAVR

1165
00:42:47,119 --> 00:42:48,159
without even informing us.

1166
00:42:48,559 --> 00:42:49,519
So why exactly

1167
00:42:50,039 --> 00:42:51,440
did the family suddenly agree to surgery?

1168
00:42:52,199 --> 00:42:52,599
And why

1169
00:42:52,599 --> 00:42:53,400
transapical TAVR?

1170
00:42:53,880 --> 00:42:54,800
I asked Liu Dong.

1171
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:56,039
It was Ouyang Da.
